---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Netherlands Work Visa Insurance Guide 2025 | Kennismigrant & 30% Ruling";
const description = "Complete guide to Netherlands work visa insurance requirements. Covers Kennismigrant (Highly Skilled Migrant), 30% tax ruling, Dutch health insurance, and expat coverage in the Netherlands.";

const tocItems = [
  { id: "overview", label: "Overview" },
  { id: "quick-decision", label: "Is This Right for You?" },
  { id: "official-requirements", label: "Official Requirements" },
  { id: "insurance-requirements", label: "Insurance Requirements" },
  { id: "recommended-providers", label: "Recommended Providers" },
  { id: "costs", label: "Costs Breakdown" },
  { id: "application-timeline", label: "Application Timeline" },
  { id: "scenarios", label: "Real-World Scenarios" },
  { id: "common-mistakes", label: "Common Mistakes" },
  { id: "healthcare-access", label: "Healthcare Access" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQs" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Final Verdict" }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <PageShell
    title="Netherlands Work Visa Insurance Guide"
    subtitle="Your complete guide to working legally in the Netherlands with proper health coverage"
    heroImage="/images/countries/netherlands-hero-bg.png"
    tocItems={tocItems}
  >
    <!-- Quick Facts Box -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Quick Facts: Netherlands Work Visa</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><strong>Main Visa Type:</strong> Kennismigrant (Highly Skilled Migrant)</div>
        <div><strong>Initial Duration:</strong> Up to 5 years</div>
        <div><strong>Salary Threshold:</strong> €5,331/month (30+ years old)</div>
        <div><strong>Processing Time:</strong> 2-4 weeks</div>
        <div><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Dutch insurance mandatory (basisverzekering)</div>
        <div><strong>Tax Benefit:</strong> 30% ruling (tax-free allowance)</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The Netherlands is one of Europe's most expat-friendly countries, with the Kennismigrant (Highly Skilled Migrant) scheme offering a fast-track visa for qualified professionals. Unlike most European work permits, the Kennismigrant doesn't require a labor market test—if you meet the salary threshold and your employer is a recognized sponsor, approval is nearly automatic.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The famous 30% ruling is a major draw: qualifying expats receive 30% of their salary tax-free for up to 5 years, significantly boosting take-home pay. Combined with high English proficiency across the country, the Netherlands has become a hub for international companies and tech startups.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Dutch health insurance works differently from most countries. Once registered as a resident, you must purchase a basisverzekering (basic health insurance) from a private insurer within 4 months. Your employer often handles this as part of onboarding. The system offers excellent care but requires understanding its unique structure.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Decision Guide -->
    <section id="quick-decision" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Is a Netherlands Work Visa Right for You?</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit If You...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Have a job offer from a recognized sponsor company</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Earn above €5,331/month (or €4,055 if under 30)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Want the 30% ruling tax advantage</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Prefer English as working language</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Work in tech, finance, or skilled professions</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives If...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Your salary is below the threshold</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Employer isn't a recognized IND sponsor</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You want to be self-employed (separate visa)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You need specialist care not in basisverzekering</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You prefer warmer climate (Dutch weather is gray)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Official Requirements -->
    <section id="official-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Official Requirements</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa Categories</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Visa Type", "Duration", "Salary Requirement (2025)", "Best For"]}
        rows={[
          ["Kennismigrant (30+)", "Up to 5 years", "€5,331/month gross", "Experienced professionals"],
          ["Kennismigrant (under 30)", "Up to 5 years", "€4,055/month gross", "Young professionals"],
          ["EU Blue Card", "Up to 4 years", "€6,245/month gross", "EU-wide mobility needs"],
          ["Intra-Corporate Transfer", "Up to 3 years", "Varies", "Company transfers"],
          ["Orientation Year (Zoekjaar)", "1 year", "None (job search)", "Recent graduates, researchers"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Eligibility Criteria</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Requirement", "Details", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Recognized Sponsor", "Employer must be IND-registered", "Most large companies are sponsors"],
          ["Salary Threshold", "Age-dependent minimum", "Updated annually (January)"],
          ["Employment Contract", "Dutch law contract", "Must specify gross salary"],
          ["No Labor Market Test", "Not required for Kennismigrant", "Major advantage vs other EU countries"],
          ["Education", "Not formally required", "Salary threshold implies qualification"],
          ["Health Insurance", "Must obtain within 4 months", "Dutch basisverzekering mandatory"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">30% Ruling Eligibility</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">To qualify for the 30% ruling, you must be recruited from abroad (lived 150km+ from Dutch border for 16 of 24 months before employment) and have specific expertise not readily available in the Netherlands. The minimum taxable salary is €46,107 (2025) or €35,048 for under-30s with a master's degree.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Required Documents</h3>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Valid passport</strong> – At least 6 months validity</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Employment contract</strong> – Signed, meeting salary threshold</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Antecedents certificate</strong> – Employer declaration on background</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Passport photos</strong> – Dutch biometric requirements</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>TB test result</strong> – Required for some nationalities post-arrival</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mt-4">Note: Your employer (recognized sponsor) submits most documents directly to IND. The process is employer-driven, not applicant-driven.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Insurance Requirements -->
    <section id="insurance-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-red-800 font-medium">⚠️ Dutch Health Insurance is Mandatory</p>
        <p class="text-red-700 text-sm mt-1">Within 4 months of registering at the gemeente (municipality), you must purchase a basisverzekering from a Dutch health insurer. Failure to do so results in automatic enrollment by CAK with a fine of 130% of premiums owed.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">How Dutch Health Insurance Works</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Component", "What It Is", "Cost (2025)"]}
        rows={[
          ["Basisverzekering", "Mandatory basic insurance (same coverage all insurers)", "€130-180/month"],
          ["Eigen risico", "Mandatory deductible", "€385/year"],
          ["Aanvullende verzekering", "Optional add-ons (dental, physio, glasses)", "€10-50/month"],
          ["Zorgtoeslag", "Government subsidy (income-based)", "Up to €123/month back"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">What Basisverzekering Covers</h3>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Included in Basic</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• GP (huisarts) visits - no cost</li>
            <li>• Hospital care</li>
            <li>• Specialist care (with referral)</li>
            <li>• Prescription medications</li>
            <li>• Mental healthcare (basis GGZ)</li>
            <li>• Maternity care</li>
            <li>• Emergency care</li>
            <li>• Physical therapy (limited sessions)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Requires Add-on (Aanvullend)</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Dental care (adults)</li>
            <li>• Glasses/contact lenses</li>
            <li>• Extra physical therapy sessions</li>
            <li>• Alternative medicine</li>
            <li>• Orthodontics</li>
            <li>• Podiatry</li>
            <li>• Travel vaccinations</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">The Eigen Risico (Deductible)</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The €385 annual deductible applies to most care except GP visits, maternity, and children under 18. This means your first €385 of specialist care, hospital visits, or prescriptions each year comes out of pocket. After that, insurance covers 100%.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">Gap Coverage: First 4 Months</p>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-1">You have 4 months to obtain Dutch insurance after municipality registration. During this gap, travel insurance or international coverage is wise. Some employers provide temporary coverage as part of relocation packages.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Recommended Providers -->
    <section id="recommended-providers" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Dutch Health Insurers (Basisverzekering)</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        All Dutch insurers must offer identical basisverzekering coverage—the only differences are price, customer service, and add-on options. Compare annually during the switch period (November-December).
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Insurer", "Monthly Premium", "Expat-Friendly", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Zilveren Kruis", "€135-150", "Good", "Largest insurer, good app"],
          ["CZ", "€140-155", "Good", "Strong hospital network"],
          ["Menzis", "€130-145", "Average", "Budget-friendly"],
          ["VGZ", "€135-150", "Good", "Covers expat clinics"],
          ["ONVZ", "€145-165", "Excellent", "English support, expat focus"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">International Providers (Supplemental/Gap Coverage)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Provider", "Best For", "Monthly Cost", "Key Features"]}
        rows={[
          ["Cigna Global", "Executives, global mobility", "€200-450", "Worldwide coverage, direct billing"],
          ["Allianz Care", "Long-term expats", "€150-350", "EU-regulated, good NL network"],
          ["Aetna International", "US expats", "€180-400", "US coverage integration"],
          ["SafetyWing", "Transition period", "€50-100", "Short-term gap coverage"],
          ["BUPA Global", "Mental health focus", "€180-380", "No therapy limits"]
        ]}
      />

      <CTABox
        title="Compare Health Insurance for Netherlands"
        description="Get quotes for Dutch basisverzekering or international supplemental coverage for your move to the Netherlands."
        buttonText="Compare Plans"
        buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Costs Breakdown -->
    <section id="costs" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa & Setup Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Cost (EUR)", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["MVV (entry visa)", "€210", "If required for your nationality"],
          ["Residence permit", "€350", "Kennismigrant permit fee"],
          ["30% ruling application", "€0", "Free to apply (employer submits)"],
          ["BSN registration", "€0", "Free at gemeente"],
          ["TB test (if required)", "€90", "GGD appointment"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <p class="text-green-800 font-medium">Employer Usually Covers</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 text-sm mt-1">Most recognized sponsors cover visa fees, IND costs, and often relocation expenses. Confirm with your employer what's included in your relocation package.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Health Insurance Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Monthly Cost", "Annual Total", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Basisverzekering", "€130-180", "€1,560-2,160", "Mandatory for all residents"],
          ["Eigen risico", "€32 (effective)", "€385", "Deductible for most care"],
          ["Aanvullende (dental/physio)", "€15-40", "€180-480", "Optional but recommended"],
          ["Zorgtoeslag (subsidy)", "-€0 to -€123", "Up to -€1,476", "Income-dependent rebate"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Living Costs (Monthly)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Amsterdam", "Other Cities", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Rent (1BR)", "€1,500-2,200", "€1,000-1,500", "Housing shortage is severe"],
          ["Utilities", "€150-250", "€120-200", "Gas prices volatile"],
          ["Transport", "€100 (OV-chipkaart)", "€80-100", "Excellent public transit"],
          ["Food", "€350-500", "€300-400", "Groceries + occasional dining"],
          ["Healthcare (OOP)", "€160-220", "€160-220", "Insurance + deductible spread"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">30% Ruling Impact</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">With 30% ruling, a €70,000 salary means only €49,000 is taxed. At ~40% marginal rate, you save roughly €8,400/year in taxes. This makes Netherlands competitive with lower-tax countries despite headline rates.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Application Timeline -->
    <section id="application-timeline" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Timeline</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 1-2</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Job Offer & Contract</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Accept offer from recognized sponsor. Sign employment contract meeting salary threshold. Employer prepares IND application.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 2-4</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">IND Application</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Employer submits application to IND. Decision typically within 2 weeks for recognized sponsors. Residence permit approved.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 4-6</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">MVV Collection (if required)</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">If your nationality requires MVV, collect visa sticker at Dutch embassy/consulate in your country. Some nationalities skip this step.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 6-8</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Arrival & BSN Registration</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Arrive in Netherlands. Register at gemeente (municipality) within 5 days of finding housing. Receive BSN (citizen service number).</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 8-10</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Residence Permit & Biometrics</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Appointment at IND for biometrics. Receive residence permit card (verblijfsvergunning) by mail within 2 weeks. Now fully legal to work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Month 1-4</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Health Insurance & Bank</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Open Dutch bank account (BSN required). Purchase basisverzekering within 4 months. Apply for zorgtoeslag if eligible. 30% ruling application submitted by employer to tax office.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Real-World Scenarios -->
    <section id="scenarios" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Software Engineer from India</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Raj, 28, joins Amsterdam tech company. €65,000 salary. Kennismigrant processed in 10 days. 30% ruling approved—effective salary €91,000 tax treatment. ONVZ insurance with English support. Delighted with work-life balance.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Fast process, major tax savings, excellent expat infrastructure</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Finance Professional from UK</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Emma, 35, post-Brexit move to Amsterdam bank. No MVV needed (UK nationals). Residence permit in 3 weeks. 30% ruling approved. Shocked by housing prices—spent €2,100/month on small apartment. Dutch insurance easy via employer.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Smooth process, but housing market was challenging</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Researcher at University</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Dr. Kim, 32, postdoc at TU Delft. Lower academic salary (€4,200/month) qualifies for reduced Kennismigrant threshold for researchers. 30% ruling approved despite lower salary. Dutch healthcare covered pregnancy fully.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Special provisions for researchers make it accessible</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Startup Employee - Non-Recognized Sponsor</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Alex, 29, joins early-stage startup. Company wasn't IND-recognized sponsor yet. Had to wait 4 weeks for sponsor registration before visa application. Total process took 3 months instead of 1. Worth it for equity.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Delays if employer isn't already a recognized sponsor</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Family Relocation</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">The Petrov family moves for father's IT role. Wife and 2 children included in single application. All get residence permits. Children's healthcare free (no eigen risico under 18). Found housing in Almere (cheaper than Amsterdam).</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Family-friendly process, kids covered without extra cost</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">30% Ruling Denied</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Marcus, 40, previously worked for same company's UK office. Lived in Brussels (within 150km of Dutch border) for 2 years before transfer. 30% ruling denied due to proximity requirement. Still got Kennismigrant, but no tax benefit.</p>
          <p class="text-red-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: 150km border rule strictly enforced—lost significant tax benefit</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">1. Not Getting Dutch Insurance Within 4 Months</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">You're legally required to have basisverzekering within 4 months of BSN registration. CAK will auto-enroll you with penalties if you don't. Set a reminder immediately after gemeente registration.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">2. Assuming 30% Ruling is Automatic</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">The 30% ruling requires separate application to the tax office (Belastingdienst) and has strict eligibility criteria. You must apply within 4 months of starting work. If you lived within 150km of the Netherlands before, you likely won't qualify.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">3. Underestimating the Housing Crisis</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Amsterdam and other cities have severe housing shortages. Start searching before arrival. Budget 40-50% more than expected. Many expats live in temporary housing for months. Some employers offer relocation housing support—negotiate this.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">4. Not Understanding the Eigen Risico</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">The €385 deductible surprises many expats. GP visits are free, but your first specialist visit, hospital care, or prescription each year costs you until €385 is met. Budget for this, especially if you have ongoing health needs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">5. Skipping Dental Add-on Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Basisverzekering does NOT cover adult dental care. A filling can cost €100-200 out of pocket. Add €10-20/month for dental coverage (tandverzekering) unless you're confident in your dental health.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Healthcare Access -->
    <section id="healthcare-access" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare System Access</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Dutch healthcare is GP-centric. Your huisarts (GP) is the gatekeeper to all care. You cannot see a specialist without GP referral except in emergencies. This takes adjustment for expats from systems with direct specialist access, but it keeps costs down and ensures coordinated care.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">How to Access Care</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Care Type", "How to Access", "Cost"]}
        rows={[
          ["GP (Huisarts)", "Register with local practice, book online/phone", "€0 (no eigen risico)"],
          ["Specialist", "GP referral required", "Eigen risico applies"],
          ["Emergency (Spoedeisende Hulp)", "Go directly or call 112", "€0 for genuine emergencies"],
          ["Huisartsenpost", "After-hours GP (evenings/weekends)", "€0 (no eigen risico)"],
          ["Mental Health", "GP referral to GGZ", "Eigen risico applies"],
          ["Pharmacy", "Prescription from GP/specialist", "Eigen risico applies"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Finding a GP (Huisarts)</h3>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">GP Shortage Warning</p>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-1">Many GP practices in Amsterdam, Rotterdam, and other cities are full and not accepting new patients. Start searching immediately upon arrival. Zorgkaart Nederland website helps find practices with openings. Some expat-focused practices exist but may be more expensive.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Steps to Register</h4>
        <ol class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700 list-decimal list-inside">
          <li>Get BSN from gemeente registration</li>
          <li>Purchase basisverzekering</li>
          <li>Search for GP practices accepting patients (Zorgkaart Nederland)</li>
          <li>Call or email practice to request registration</li>
          <li>Complete intake questionnaire and appointment</li>
          <li>Receive practice details and after-hours (huisartsenpost) instructions</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Expat-Friendly Clinics</h3>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Amsterdam</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Expat Health (international staff)</li>
            <li>• TCA Huisartsen (expat-focused)</li>
            <li>• Medisch Centrum Olympisch Stadion</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Other Cities</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• International Health Centre Rotterdam</li>
            <li>• Lairesse Medical Centre (The Hague)</li>
            <li>• Eindhoven Expat Center (referrals)</li>
